ase is Waiting: transitions to Active, sets `countdown_ends_at = now + 60`\n    97→- Registered module in `instructions/mod.rs` and added `join_round` to `lib.rs`\n    98→- Extended TestContext with `player2` keypair + `player2Program` for testing joins from a different wallet\n    99→- Added `joinRound()` instruction helper\n   100→- Added 6 bankrun tests:\n   101→  - 2nd player joins and triggers countdown (Waiting → Active)\n   102→  - 3rd player joins during Active phase without re-triggering countdown\n   103→  - Player can join with multiple entries (escrow balance verified)\n   104→  - Rejects duplicate player (PlayerAlreadyInRound)\n   105→  - Rejects 21st player (MaxPlayersReached) — creates 20 players then verifies 21st is rejected\n   106→  - Rejects join when phase is Locked (placeholder — full test deferred to start_spin iteration)\n   107→\n   108→**Verification**: `anchor test --skip-local-validator --skip-deploy` — **passed** (43 tests, 0 failures). All existing coinflip + platform tests still pass.\n   109→\n   110→**Status**: Done\n   111→\n   112→## Iteration 4 — 2026-02-26T22:28:08Z — OK\n   113→- **Log**: iteration-004.log\n   114→\n   115→## Iteration 5 — buy_more_entries instruction + bankrun tests\n   116→\n   117→**Item**: Phase A, item 5 — `buy_more_entries` instruction\n   118→\n   119→**What was done**:\n   120→- Created `src/instructions/buy_more_entries.rs`:\n   121→  - `BuyMoreEntries` accounts struct with `#[instruction(tier: u8, round_number: u64)]`\n   122→  - Round PDA verified via seeds constraint (same seeds as create_round/join_round)\n   123→  - Config PDA read-only (pause check only)\n   124→  - Validates: phase is Waiting or Active, player already in round (PlayerNotInRound error), num_entries > 0\n   125→  - Calculates `total_cost = entry_amount × num_entries`, transfers to escrow\n   126→  - Finds player by index in Vec, increments their entries count and total_entries\n   127→- Registered module in `instructions/mod.rs` and added `buy_more_entries` to `lib.rs`\n   128→- Added `buyMoreEntries()` instruction helper to test file\n   129→- Added 4 bankrun tests:\n   130→  - Existing player buys more entries (verifies count 1→4, escrow balance)\n   131→  - Works during Active phase (after countdown triggered by 2nd player)\n   132→  - Rejects player not in round (PlayerNotInRound)\n   133→  - Rejects zero entries (ZeroEntries)\n   134→\n   135→**Verification**: `anchor test --skip-local-validator --skip-deploy` — **passed** (47 tests, 0 failures). All existing coinflip + platform tests still pass.\n   136→\n   137→**Status**: Done\n   138→\n   139→\n   140→## Iteration 5 — 2026-02-26T22:32:58Z — OK\n   141→- **Log**: iteration-005.log\n   142→\n   143→## Iteration 6 — start_spin instruction + bankrun tests\n   144→\n   145→**Item**: Phase A, item 6 — `start_spin` instruction\n   146→\n   147→**What was done**:\n   148→- Created `src/instructions/start_spin.rs`:\n   149→  - `StartSpin` accounts struct with `#[instruction(tier: u8, round_number: u64)]`\n   150→  - Round PDA verified via seeds constraint (same seeds as other instructions)\n   151→  - Config PDA read-only (for bump verification)\n   152→  - Includes all Orao VRF accounts (orao_program, orao_network_state, orao_treasury, orao_random) as UncheckedAccounts\n   153→  - Idempotent: if phase is already Locked, returns Ok without error\n   154→  - Validates: phase must be Active (rejects Waiting and other non-Active/Locked phases)\n   155→  - Validates: `clock.unix_timestamp >= countdown_ends_at` (CountdownNotExpired error)\n   156→  - Uses shared lifecycle::transition(Active → Locked) for validation\n   157→  - Calls `vrf_orao::request_orao_randomness()` with round PDA key as seed\n   158→  - Updates: phase → Locked, locked_at, resolve_deadline (now + 120s), vrf_request_key\n   159→- Registered module in `instructions/mod.rs` and added `start_spin` to `lib.rs`\n   160→- Updated test infrastructure in `lordofrngs.ts`:\n   161→  - Ad